HEADWORD: High-stepper
<hw>High"-step`per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A horse that
moves with a high step or proud gait; hence, a person having a proud
bearing.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

